  "body": "I'm using a library that provides a component called InputPassword which returns an input area.\n\nI need to place a `<label>` block right beneath the `<input>` block for some animations to work. So far I've made it possible via the following:\n\n```\n<InputPassword className=\"input__field input__field--kohana password\">\n    <label className=\"input__label input__label--kohana\">\n        <i className={\"fa fa-fw icon icon--kohana fa-lock\" }></i>\n        <span className=\"input__label-content input__label-content--kohana\">Password</span>\n    </label>\n</InputPassword>\n```\n\nWorks like a charm! \n\nHowever, my console complains with the following message on every keypress:\n`Warning: input is a void element tag and must not have 'children' or use 'props.dangerouslySetInnerHTML'. Check the render method of InputPassword.`\n\nHow can I avoid this error?\n\nSimply rewriting in this way does not do the trick:\n\n```\n<InputPassword className=\"input__field input__field--kohana password\" />\n<label className=\"input__label input__label--kohana\">\n    <i className={\"fa fa-fw icon icon--kohana fa-lock\" }></i>\n    <span className=\"input__label-content input__label-content--kohana\">Password</span>\n</label>\n```\n",
